Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.46,0:00:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You found a job as a waitress\Nand got a place to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.56,0:00:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But this bed is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.63,0:00:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It sinks in this far\Nwhen I get on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.97,0:00:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be able to support\Nyour weight if you slept here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.74,0:00:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll sleep on this bed.\NYou should sleep on that sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.58,0:00:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no place\Nfor you to sleep here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.38,0:00:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to Dr. Reichwein\Nin Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.52,0:00:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you\Nhave to go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.99,0:00:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to go to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.09,0:00:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How will you learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.76,0:00:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're teaching me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.93,0:00:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just about your studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.53,0:00:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to make\Nany friends living like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.03,0:00:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I have friends. You and Tenma.\NBesides, you'll be lonely without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.41,0:01:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you should\Ngo back to Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.51,0:01:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.49,0:01:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on, Nina.\NAre you going there today, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.29,0:01:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!\NYou should give it up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.43,0:01:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been going to\Nthe same place everyday!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.80,0:01:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always the same ! You're\Nnot going to remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.57,0:01:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.16,0:02:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We lived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.73,0:03:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and I. ..and Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.38,0:03:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That day, Johan was dragged\Ndown these stairs and taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.73,0:03:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Stop! Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom ! Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.27,0:03:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Nina is my name now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.90,0:03:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What was I called then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.91,0:03:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina? Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:04:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The car they put Johan\Ninto went along this road.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.83,0:04:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't keep secrets from him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.20,0:04:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They gathered children here\Nand held what they called "recitals."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.21,0:04:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The lock's broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.02,0:04:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They were trying to create\Na "superior pupil" here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.73,0:04:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a "superior pupil"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.94,0:04:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They also...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.06,0:05:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.63,0:05:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He went through\Nthe rose bushes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.60,0:05:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.27,0:05:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.37,0:05:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.71,0:05:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.18,0:05:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.98,0:05:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I.. .was waiting in this room...\Nfor Mom to come home...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.69,0:05:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for Johan to come home...\Nwhile I was reading this picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}People can become\Nwhatever they want to be.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.77,0:05:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.14,0:05:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonaparta held the recitals\Nat the Red Rose Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.87,0:06:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I read one of his books as\NI waited Johan to come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.58,0:06:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I smiled as I faced\Nthe open door and said...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Welcome home.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.49,0:06:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.63,0:06:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.10,0:06:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.\NWelcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.54,0:06:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.\NWelcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.60,0:06:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home. Welcome home.\NWelcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now then, come here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.21,0:06:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The door won't open!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The door won't open\Neven when I say, "Welcome home !"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.95,0:06:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't open!\NIt won't open!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.66,0:06:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because I ...\NThat's because I ...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.66,0:06:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember! I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.56,0:06:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.53,0:06:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to remember!\NYou don't have to remember anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.07,0:06:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the same!\NI have a lot of bad memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.54,0:07:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't have to\Nremember any of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.87,0:07:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, I'll go to Dr. Reichwein !\NYou too Nina, let's go back together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.68,0:07:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do as Tenma said!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll make fun memories\Nfrom now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.37,0:07:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, Chief Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.21,0:07:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All I can do is sit next to\Na detective and just listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.01,0:07:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.34,0:07:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We're trying to satisfy\Nyour requests as best we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.38,0:07:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"As best you can"? In addition,\Nthere's a thirty-minute limit per person!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.82,0:07:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just listening to them\Nshould be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.62,0:07:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that we are helping you\Nthis much is quite extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We went through\Na lot of trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.53,0:08:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and were finally allowed to\Nquestion these five witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.73,0:08:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.97,0:08:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have taken the opportunity\Nto get as many testimonies...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.34,0:08:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're naïve.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.37,0:08:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Those "children of the recitals" probably\Ndon't want to talk about their pasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the large amount of human\Nremains that we discovered definitely
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,has something to do with the former\NCzechoslovakian secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.62,0:08:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.09,0:08:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth about things like this\Nusually remains a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.97,0:08:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. He's the detective\Nin charge of the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.70,0:08:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Mr. Verdemann.\NHe's the lawyer from Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.44,0:08:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.84,0:08:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Detective Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.18,0:08:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I prepared the questions in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.08,0:08:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do exactly as I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.58,0:08:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You will sit with me\Nonly as an observer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.53,0:09:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Number 3 Cerveny Street,\Na.k.a. "The Red Rose Mansion."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's burned down.\NCurrently, it looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.34,0:09:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is no mistake\Nthat you participated
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.51,0:09:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the "recitals" here in 1968,\Nright, Mr. Erno?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.91,0:09:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.91,0:09:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard of\NFranz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.45,0:09:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you please be quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.39,0:09:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We're running out of time,\Naren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.95,0:09:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to be thorough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to be thorough\Nand end up with no information?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.13,0:09:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know how hard\Nwe worked to get this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.20,0:09:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.93,0:09:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this mansion was\Nmy emotional foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.20,0:09:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon seeing this image\Nof it burned down,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.74,0:09:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that I would\Nfeel sadder, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.21,0:09:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel nostalgic about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.98,0:09:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nostalgic?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.42,0:10:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. This was like\Na school to you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.89,0:10:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann, please be quiet!\NThe questions that I prepared are...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.62,0:10:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.16,0:10:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadness... Nostalgia.. .\NI don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.60,0:10:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotional scars?\NWhat do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.90,0:10:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, is there anything\Nthat affects you now
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because you participated\Nin those "recitals"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.51,0:10:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.68,0:10:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What about your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.98,0:10:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to answer.\NYou have that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.96,0:10:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there weren't any big problems\Nbetween my wife and me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My children... My oldest son and\Nmy second son. ..committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't really\Nhave any problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But for some reason, they...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why they\Ncommitted suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.48,0:11:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying all your questions\Nare "by the book."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.65,0:11:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How much have you been able to\Nget out of anyone so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.56,0:11:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a typical youth of today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.49,0:11:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably try to ask girls out\N"by the book" as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.63,0:11:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're acting like a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.97,0:11:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a father, but I wouldn't\Nlike to have a father like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Will the next person come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.68,0:11:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of the "recitals", huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.38,0:11:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you can recall,\Nno matter how trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.52,0:11:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"The God of Peace\Nwas very busy."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.82,0:11:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.59,0:11:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"He blew his trumpet every day. He didn't\Nhave the time to look in the mirror."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.89,0:11:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe's {\i1}The God of Peace.{\i0}\NYou know it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.96,0:11:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I kind of remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.87,0:11:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Aside from that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.67,0:12:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked the one about the Monster of\Nthe West and the Monster of the East.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.44,0:12:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you like about those stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.71,0:12:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... How should I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like I was being taken\Nto a different world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.78,0:12:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A different world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.15,0:12:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,crying, being happy,\Nand being afraid...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose it felt like all of\Nthose things just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you feel that way\Nabout this book?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.99,0:12:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI didn't feel a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.67,0:12:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't need\Nyour own name anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.57,0:12:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true freedom.\NThat's what it felt like.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you feel like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.01,0:12:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta taught you\Nto feel like that, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.31,0:12:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that the name of\Nthe person who held the recitals?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.08,0:12:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you clearly remember\Nfrom the recitals, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.09,0:12:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.46,0:12:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, a man came\Nto visit that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.76,0:13:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he was\Nfrom a radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.97,0:13:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that he liked the song,\N{\i1}Over the Rainbow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.64,0:13:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me about\N{\i1}The Wizard of Oz.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.27,0:13:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of man was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.58,0:13:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me! Tell me about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.91,0:13:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.28,0:13:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,– Tell me!\N– Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.88,0:13:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.82,0:13:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.05,0:13:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like your personal emotions\Nare influencing the questioning!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.29,0:13:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is personal for you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the young detective\Nthat was falsely being accused
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.10,0:13:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for the series of crimes\Ncommitted by the secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.13,0:13:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're him, aren't you,\NDetective Suk?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.87,0:13:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're desperate to prove\Nyour innocence. Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.77,0:13:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The same goes for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was imprisoned\Nfor being an East German spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I continued to believe that\Nhe was falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.72,0:13:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But my father really was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.92,0:14:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I could no longer believe in anything\Nafter I found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.66,0:14:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I no longer believe in\Nanything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.96,0:14:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, I am pursuing a case involving\Na man who has been falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.03,0:14:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of that, I have once again\Nfound something that I can believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.51,0:14:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The man from the radio station\Nthat the witness talked about...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.11,0:14:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.91,0:14:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My father might have participated\Nin the brainwashing experiments
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that happened at\Nthe "Red Rose Mansion."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to find out the real truth,\Nyou mustn't look away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, can I go home already?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.56,0:14:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.46,0:14:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,About that man I told you about.. .\NHe told me, "Get out of here...fast."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.24,0:14:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"There is definitely a wonderful place\Nover the rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.34,0:14:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's where your family is"'\Nhe said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.48,0:14:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dorothy from The Wizard of Oz\Ngets to go home in the end."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.42,0:15:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"You must get away\Nfrom here fast"' he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.56,0:15:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I cut all ties\Nwith that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that enough?\NMy wife and kids are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.16,0:15:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.04,0:15:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We mustn't look away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.48,0:15:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.11,0:15:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two more witnesses\Nleft to question.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.92,0:15:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Let's continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.86,0:15:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Dieter.\NStop spacing out and hold it steady!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.43,0:15:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your study desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.80,0:15:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.40,0:15:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina doesn't want to talk about\Nthat happened in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.21,0:15:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,According to what\NI heard from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,she's probably recovered\Nquite a bit of her memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.08,0:16:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems like\Nthe brakes were hit
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.18,0:16:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,right before her memories fully\Ncame back to her, thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.92,0:16:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I do something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.22,0:16:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.39,0:16:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, you did a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's finish this quickly and\Nhave some weisswurst and beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.23,0:16:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We ate all the weisswurst\Nlast night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.50,0:16:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. That's right.\NOh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.41,0:16:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.01,0:16:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We bought your favorite,\Nweisswurst.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.58,0:16:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How considerate of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.58,0:16:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.78,0:16:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dr. Reichwein, how are you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.72,0:16:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}– I'm sorry for not{\i0}\N– Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.15,0:16:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}– Contacting you for so long.{\i0}\N– Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.96,0:16:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sorry for making you worry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.89,0:16:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm safe.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dr. Reichwein, to be honest,\NI would like to ask you a favor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.43,0:16:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sure you know a woman by\Nthe name of Eva Heinemann.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right now, she's being pursued\Nby a certain organization.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've sent her in your direction.\NPlease take care of Eva.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.71,0:17:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And please take care of\NNina and Dieter.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.58,0:17:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm almost finished.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.18,0:17:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I think this is the only way\Nto put an end to the case.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.36,0:17:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sincerely, Kenzo Tenma."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.76,0:17:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This letter came\Nthree days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's still no sign of Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.10,0:17:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where was this mailed from?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.84,0:17:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't see the postmark\Nvery clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.14,0:17:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you look it up, Karl?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.01,0:17:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do that,\Nwe'll know where Tenma is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.88,0:17:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But.. .I'm a bit worried\Nabout this last sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.72,0:17:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"I think this is the only way\Nto put an end to the case."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.13,0:18:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then,\Nlet's finish this study desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.37,0:18:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I drank a beer,\Nso my hand might slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.24,0:18:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.91,0:18:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can almost\Nremember everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.21,0:18:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When you do remember everything...\NAre you prepared for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.28,0:18:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.45,0:18:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Use whatever method necessary\Nto bring my memories back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I don't want to do anything.\NBut if you really want to...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.70,0:18:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You're fine with this,\Nright, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.44,0:18:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Dr. Gillen. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.44,0:18:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever I say under hypnotherapy.. .\Nmight be incredibly terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.68,0:18:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you face it with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.12,0:18:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'll be fine.\NLet's face this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.19,0:19:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now close your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.76,0:19:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a deep breath and\Nrelax your whole body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.87,0:19:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your mother like?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.24,0:19:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother...she's nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.48,0:19:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,songs. ..singing voice...\Na beautiful singing voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.85,0:19:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell of pea soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.72,0:19:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What about your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.99,0:19:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My father... My father is...\Na government soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.66,0:19:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A government soldier?\NHave you ever met him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.00,0:19:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never met him.\NMy mother told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.07,0:19:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My father.. .was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.44,0:19:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother. ..participated in\Nanti-government activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.01,0:20:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father was killed,\Nand your mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.42,0:20:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,an activist who participated in\Nanti-government activities, escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.05,0:20:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was she\Nrunning away from?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.39,0:20:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The three frogs...we hid.. . but a\Nman in glasses caught my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.30,0:20:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brother was caught, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.47,0:20:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.14,0:20:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people were dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.14,0:20:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Did your brother see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts! It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.01,0:20:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts! The rose thorns...\NIt hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.58,0:20:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Welcome home.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.92,0:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.43,0:20:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.69,0:20:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out where Tenma\Nmailed his letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.76,0:20:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.83,0:20:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.43,0:20:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina? You've remembered everything,\Nhaven't you, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.14,0:20:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm.. .not Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.71,0:20:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.61,0:21:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.11,0:21:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.08,0:21:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.48,0:21:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.88,0:21:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.82,0:21:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right.\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.79,0:21:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.32,0:21:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.16,0:21:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.43,0:21:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.97,0:21:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm going to clap\Nmy hands right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're going to\Nwake up from your trance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.44,0:21:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.41,0:21:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.28,0:21:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I say something\Nterrible just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.39,0:21:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.19,0:21:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,While you were hypnotized,\Nyou refused to talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.49,0:21:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But you remember everything now,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.34,0:22:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dr. Reichwein, Dieter...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.71,0:22:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please forgive me\Nfor leaving suddenly.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.11,0:22:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm going to Frankfurt,\Nwhere Tenma is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.42,0:22:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I know everything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.25,0:22:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who I am. Where Johan has\Ncome from and where he's headed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.66,0:22:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I go, I can end everything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.23,0:22:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I go, I can save Tenma.{\i0}
